-- update_db.sh 

When changing the petascope database, put all changes in a file updateN.sql,
where N is the next number following the last update.

 * To setup petascope database for the first time: ./update_db.sh 0
 * To upgrade the database starting from a specific update number N, use ./update_db.sh N

IMPORTANT: don't execute update_db.sh with sh, but with bash. Best is to
chmod +x update_db.sh, and execute it with ./update_db.sh


-- gensql_uos.pl

usage: $ perl gensql_uos.pl <file> <coverageID>

where <file> : 3D Point Cloud file saved in UOS Format (contains x y z values separated by whitespace)
	  <coverageID> : MultiPoint coverageID from ps_coverage to which this pointCloud refers to.
	

-- droptables.sql

add DROP command at the end for any new tables added further.
when deleting; rename this file to updateX.sql where X is the last (to be) number
run $bash update_db.sh X

